[{"id":27231,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Hzqs6XmRkP3DMBOEymvWEY39VMFEE332kuquVTy5c3I.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/NrUis3lLp2_7eX-ytYmW4dqMFwjW9oBu_obzohhUhOA.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/yc_N02L-ogmb2wbS8nKQu1-FJ0aVVSGdngMxVcz2jFw.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/TiyAL0mSfx7hgeOc04U2PZP7qwR6hc5Duejckmzdy6k.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9CKrAXTiPbAwCLL2Vmy8eAiqv9n-XTjsM1Q6ZwuI4gg.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27261,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["A-IV, B-III, C-II, D-I","A-III, B-I, C-II, D-IV","A-I, B-III, C-IV, D-II","A-III, B-I, C-IV, D-II"],"answer":3,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Coupling reaction between benzene diazonium chlorides with aniline in acidic medium takes place to give yellow colour. In this reaction the nitrogen <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;in the diazonium ion is lost and forms the bridge between two benzene rings forming an electrophilic substitution reaction.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c3fa8f4d-49df-41ea-b1a1-4283c2e002c1.png\" style=\"width: 508px; height: 114px;\" /></p><p>Fluoro benzene is prepared by treating benzene diazonium chloride with fluoro boric acid. This reaction produces diazonium fluoroborate which on heating produces fluorobenzene. This reaction is called Balz-Schiemann reaction.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1655d39b-ee53-4d26-87d9-b61330652897.png\" style=\"width: 354px; height: 135px;\" /></p><p>Gattermann reaction is used for obtaining chlorobenzene from benzenediazonium chloride by treating it with Cu/HCl&nbsp; respectively.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/72526328-345d-4304-b672-f1ec5dc2b099.png\" style=\"width: 359px; height: 124px;\" /></p><p>Similarly,&nbsp;Benzene diazonium chloride solution on reaction with cuprous cyanide&nbsp;and potassium&nbsp;cyanide&nbsp;gives&nbsp;benzonitrile. This reaction is known as Sandmeyer&#39;s reaction.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3d46c0d7-e4a8-4986-9ef9-f4f5e06c7349.png\" style=\"width: 328px; height: 110px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27330,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f47d4d6a-d1b1-4c16-a4a8-3d39fad7ea24-image.png\" style=\"width: 233px; height: 119px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1c93b496-82dd-48da-af5c-7700018f20ef-image.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 111px;\" />","<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e435fd62-918c-456c-b49c-9d998a71f40f-image.png\" style=\"width: 183px; height: 112px;\" /></p>","<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a582c020-c83c-4020-bf09-f11c86b09f90-image.png\" style=\"width: 217px; height: 112px;\" /></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/20de9385-93bd-4fc4-bdd2-4a1b6705fc55-f7816885-9b2e-428c-a7a4-63834dd3d00b-image.png\" style=\"width: 470px; height: 160px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (16 Mar Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27341,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>IV</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>III</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>II</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">I</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>II</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>III</mi><mo>&#60;</mo><mi>IV</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><msub><mi>PK</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></msub><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mtext>&#160;Basic strength&#160;</mtext><mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></msub></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi>b</mi></msub><mo>&#8733;</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi></math> effect <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mo>-</mo></msup></mfenced></math> density)<br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></msub><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">M</mi><mtext>&#160;effect&#160;</mtext></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mi>b</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#62;</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>PK</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&#60;</mo><mn>3</mn></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/974bf0a5-75f1-40f6-984e-bcdd77e7bef0-image.png\" style=\"width: 700px; height: 185px;\" />&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (06 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27388,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["Carbanion","Carbene","Carbocation","Carbon radical"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/nVaFyJRZoqgNwShSCMRrktpXqBqoJqd0ydcx5QfXbSU.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\nMechanism<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/K-TTkZjRcohdeFQfK5v1JieqoS2pwDO6sDCKkIpKO4U.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/SXGYCC1Yh9tA3mnKtDVnCa2wTT_ysZuyaukb8SXDzW4.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f7p-7EAp_kGE1sX_RCCygylGmLfX20e1QS37lLiwefI.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (25 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27229,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/MWs7nfTNmGRUffDaLY6VL9l4Ak5e3VIhaDR1mF4W1yI.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>, $\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CHO}$","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/yD5y2YFURCyl3aa-Crh663FsVg47U3Ss4QdiP5C8t2g.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>, $\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{COOH}$","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/H1GvJcZESStW4X_J5dycPeM89Tm-F2qVuIZZI1N7s-M.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>, $\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CHO}$","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/olvo8mfmiZY1SVkSlIPtTUiy9ui4KP7achjW90QH2Lo.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/KTioOxYJlQsT9-W-rmoT_Ca0Yo8FwaiW2QLYWObqTOs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (22 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27295,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0f94a2c8-344a-4213-9839-59ad07896cc8-a.JPG\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 195px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c3ea74e1-1294-453c-8da5-cd4a0f1770c6-b.JPG\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 166px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/220f6115-adb8-42eb-97f5-24b599327974-c.JPG\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 189px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d82ac420-d896-456c-93af-d87ceb73a0ae-d.JPG\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 147px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"All these enamines are interconvertible through their resonating structures. So most stable form is &lsquo;C&rsquo; due to steric factor. All of these has the equal resonance only differ in their geometrical configuration. The enamine in option C has bulky groups on opposite side of double bond. means they have the minimum repulsion between them.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27216,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/m3pMzR2UO89Gpk89Ty4fIRM0jLF8pvVEik0g_sMLdZQ.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/NS9UTUdcQXLGu8KxS-fDudLLelrahaaVk7fo7270Ihc.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/rjKFy5pmyEgcwcrtsq3qwK_6RJohlYGhHilTiMHgP0E.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/-meZBhCUWFPfV4oT99TkX4wFOJzyKnJF1E1C-ImKvpQ.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fD32Ss7DWy13TlWF1KOeWdYpxR_KAug_xRB4Rfz5l_4.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27230,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://cdn.quizrr.in/question-assets/jee_main_pyq/fswVHQ_F5xN-YunbTOcutIzrYlS7hqN-GD8-e11iDCw.original.fullsize_2.png\"><br>Molar mass \\(=120 \\times 12+10 \\times 1=154\\)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (22 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27358,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"Hinsberg reagent is also known as benzene sulfonyl chloride and used for detection of primary, secondary and tertiary amines. <br/><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/63bc47d6-cdf5-4b55-b6e4-14e75f3d234f-image35.png\">","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27401,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["an isocyanide","an aldehyde","a cyanide","an alcohol"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/eeFdQTfqhpsCGqpMNyxqFmP45fmdI-zdsJtDcDrBUNs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2002","image":null},{"id":27395,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["$\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{CN}$ and $3 \\mathrm{KCl}$","$\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{CONH}_2$ and $3 \\mathrm{KCl}$","$\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{NC}$ and $\\mathrm{K}_2 \\mathrm{CO}_3$","$\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{NC}$ and $3 \\mathrm{KCl}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"It is example of carbylamine reaction. so, the product will be $\\mathrm{C}_2 \\mathrm{H}_5 \\mathrm{NC}$ and $\\mathrm{KCl}$. \nHence, (D) is the correct answer.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":27300,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3e4e75ba-c184-40c3-a00d-a8cbfc889056-image.png\" style=\"width: 239px; height: 41px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ebcfc893-0f14-4d82-8c27-d010383275cb-image.png\" style=\"width: 214px; height: 132px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5065cfdc-5e93-47e0-8849-504c15ce9b3f-image.png\" style=\"width: 251px; height: 151px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ce64dc5b-c7f9-46e5-b655-61b74eb9878a-image.png\" style=\"width: 163px; height: 129px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>&nbsp;</p><p>The diazonium salt formed by aromatic primary amines are more stable than aliphatic primary amines.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9d4359ef-8191-466f-8f18-0ab399817e65-image.png\" style=\"width: 646px; height: 159px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (01 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27263,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/71134e92-6def-4dcc-ab8a-e8a8c9893f1e-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 100px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/27a57ebb-16fc-45ea-8110-81431d77fc44-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 110px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/30d39fe8-bc4f-4ccb-9794-5d6167a8e949-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 103px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0853e6a9-0b62-453e-8b82-f8263c0d3eca-image.png\" style=\"width: 400px; height: 112px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Acetanilide undergo electrophilic bromination&nbsp;with bromine in acetic acid. p-bromoacetaniide&nbsp;is the major product in this reaction.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/434e5f51-0408-45f2-a37d-5872dc7f3721.png\" style=\"width: 441px; height: 191px;\" /></p><p>Acetanilide undergo reduction reaction with lithium aluminium hydride.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e2d0e5c5-49b2-4556-8da3-dc7598682cc1.png\" style=\"width: 427px; height: 172px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (06 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27311,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["Both (A) and (R) true but (R) is not the correct<br />&nbsp;explanation of (A).","(A) is false but ( R) is true.","Both (A) and (R)&nbsp;true and (R)&nbsp;is correct<br />explanation of (A).","(A) is true but (R)&nbsp;is false."],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Gabriel phthalimide synthesis</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f6e03060-2699-40a0-985c-d2a3e2032ed5-image.png\" style=\"width: 438px; height: 350px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27236,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/pwKDMM_oQpxScI49JnNkpmsm-3kupVF4FFwJjsfECBY.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/gn4BoKhMZhA-o936JfwKrqEtoNOI_MVm89x4pjnSnfg.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/_DqUDzRi-3gTdO7V8UX4Wqm-EzWMWO6CUnqEUWuOIqI.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ZQ2F6psfWv7JSQ6WMgFcloTjeUdpeFsam5OkU-C4kyo.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8HapThtIdOkYOVm5EZ0AEj1GIQyC_Jt43kBSX7RW2AE.original.fullsize.png\"><br><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bU_K5biF7BMWqoMhQ7gJPX0aFa7eb-TgqHDp45sHQAQ.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (06 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27337,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e71ae45c-aac6-4fbd-9e40-5ab09d8b4675-image.png\" style=\"width: 139px; height: 97px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b69fec52-07bc-4dcc-bb13-ccd4f5855654-image.png\" style=\"width: 113px; height: 68px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0add7b76-ea95-4a08-a2b1-06a4c53f4c98-image.png\" style=\"width: 143px; height: 70px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cf2779df-5820-4697-9b04-16687ca35b32-image.png\" style=\"width: 154px; height: 71px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>The colour obtained is the colour of the compound formed in the reaction of aniline with&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaNO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#8203;</mo><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></math>&nbsp;at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>0</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>&nbsp;followed by coupling with &beta;-naphthol.</p><p>Aniline on reaction with<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>NaNO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></math>&nbsp;forms a diazonium salt. This diazonium salt is then coupled with &beta;-naphthol.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/efee9b3d-987d-4749-9cef-dd50f873052c-image.png\" style=\"width: 352px; height: 270px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (24 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27205,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["","","",""],"answer":3,"solution":"Cyclohexylmethylamine reacts with benzoyl chloride under basic conditions to form amide [A]:<br>cyclohexylmethyl benzoamide.<br>LiAlH₄ reduces the amide carbonyl to CH₂, converting the N-benzoyl group to a benzyl group.<br>The product [B] is a secondary amine formed by reduction:<br>cyclohexylmethyl-benzylamine ($C_6H_{11}-CH_2-NH-CH_2-C_6H_5$).<br>This structure contains secondary amine (N-H) with two carbon substituents: cyclohexylmethyl and benzyl groups.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (22 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27268,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/68b150f1-0aca-41d0-969b-1f1a09352507-9896191_1.PNG\" style=\"width: 276px; height: 180px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7e660dad-ae2b-4edd-8434-2eeac95e2d81-9896191_3.PNG\" style=\"width: 279px; height: 180px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7715cc96-6b90-4637-bbad-c7e6d84f0ef6-9896191_2.PNG\" style=\"width: 319px; height: 180px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/db2fd976-b8ae-4f15-a0fd-bbb308160a3e-9896191_4.PNG\" style=\"width: 263px; height: 180px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Nitrobenzene is reduced to aniline by passing hydrogen gas in presence of finely divided palladium and also by reduction with metals in an acidic medium. When aniline reacts with acetic anhydride in the presence of pyridine to give acetanilide. Aniline acts as a weak base, while acetic anhydride acts as electrophile.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2b7527dd-14b3-4388-8439-e7523de0f7cc-9896191_5.PNG\" style=\"width: 503px; height: 130px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27293,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["It is hinsberg&#39;s reagent","It is used to distinguish primary and secondary amines.","On treatment with secondary amine, it leads to a product, that is soluble in alkali.","It does not react with tertiary amine."],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>P-toluenesulphonyl chloride, which is also known as Hinsberg&#39;s reagent, It&nbsp;reacts with primary and secondary amines to form sulphonamides.</p><p>Tertiary amines do not react with P-toluenesulphonyl chloride.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/03623fc0-4cc4-43c5-aed1-327624c23673-9-7-20224.png\" style=\"width: 460px; height: 377px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27309,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e94a5d53-f860-4687-824c-e94676f66e4a-image.png\" style=\"width: 219px; height: 104px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b4e75511-efeb-413a-8708-ba6a76af01a0-image.png\" style=\"width: 289px; height: 112px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/db3e8770-149d-4c2e-8a5f-07e35998ade7-image.png\" style=\"width: 204px; height: 116px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/697000d4-227d-4fb5-98d4-7a97b2014b35-image.png\" style=\"width: 263px; height: 118px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7863c585-b7a5-4c17-b9bb-4cb7c48c2930-image.png\" style=\"width: 507px; height: 190px;\" /></p><p>Reduction of nitrobenzene will produce aniline which undergo coupling reaction with diazonium salt to produce yellow compound.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27389,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["$1^{\\circ}>2^{\\circ}>3^{\\circ}>\\mathrm{NH}_3$","$3^{\\circ}>2^{\\circ}>\\mathrm{NH}_3>1^{\\circ}$","$3^{\\circ}>2^{\\circ}>1^{\\circ}>\\mathrm{NH}_3$","$\\mathrm{NH}_3>1^{\\circ}>2^{\\circ}>3^{\\circ}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"The correct order of relative basicity of amines in the gas phase is $3^{\\circ}>2^{\\circ}>1^{\\circ}>\\mathrm{NH}_3$ The alkyl group releases electron and thus, tends to disperse the positive charge of the alkyl ammonium ion and therefore stabilises it. Since, $\\mathrm{NH}_4{ }^{+}$(from $\\mathrm{NH}_3$ ) has no such alkyl group, it is not stabilised to such an extent as alkylammonium ion.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (23 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27297,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/44cb28d5-6268-47cf-8745-87fc43672d7b-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 120px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4894de4c-2b85-4dcb-86cb-d2012e2471af-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 119px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a27e8ec1-23c9-43ca-a422-d847ea147af6-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 125px;\" />&nbsp;","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e9124176-5db4-45df-aac4-ec1b006c9beb-image.png\" style=\"width: 184px; height: 235px;\" />&nbsp;"],"answer":1,"solution":"Due to absence of alpha hydrogen it does not give enamine on reaction with 2 degree amine. All other molecules has alpha hydrogen present.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27377,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["IV","II","I","III"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>When the given mixture is shaken with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>HCl</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></math>amine get protonated and becomes a cation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo></msup></math><br />which does not dissolve in an organic solvent&nbsp;<br />since,&nbsp;<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0b34f7ee-906b-4fde-99a1-e105be8c321e-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 146px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1e6cd737-9608-44ab-93ee-e2622dcf8dfc-image.png\" style=\"width: 460px; height: 156px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (08 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27285,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["Cumene","Benzenediazonium chloride","Benzal chloride","Ethylene glycol ketal"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>When an aromatic primary amine is treated with nitrous (NaNO<sub>2 </sub>+ HCl) acid at 273 &ndash; 278 K, diazonium salts are obtained. These diazonium salts&nbsp;are highly reactive in nature. Upon warming with water, these diazonium salts finally hydrolyze to phenols with the liberation of nitrogen gas. Phenols can also be obtained from diazonium salts by treating it with dilute acids.<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/885ae620-3219-4cce-ad36-9462fd882dcc-image.png\" style=\"width: 330px; height: 120px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27362,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\"> </mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">b</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">u</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">p</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Gabriel phthalimide is used to prepare primary amine.<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f0756ad1-a414-40ae-9e0d-0e2ee87e2ca7-image.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 317px;\" /></p><p>In first step&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi></msub><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;reaction takes place which is possible in less stearically hindered chloride. Alkyl chloride required for other amines has high stearic hindrance therefore, stearically hindered amine can&#39;t be produced from those alkyl chlorides.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27345,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["Adenine and proline","Thymine and proline","Adenine and lysine","Adenine and thymine"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Compounds having&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>1</mn><mo>&#176;</mo></msup></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"></math>amine give carbylamine reaction with&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CHCI</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>alc</mi><mo>.</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>KOH</mi></math></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ddda49b1-b74d-4da9-b377-a68d06e85b4c-image.png\" style=\"width: 93px; height: 218px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d05fab54-07c4-458c-b524-dbc908c784fa-image.png\" style=\"width: 102px; height: 123px;\" />&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e4ac82db-4d7c-43d0-96a6-888d68a79164-image.png\" style=\"width: 127px; height: 169px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/acc2b92f-a704-4fa0-a71d-426afaca3627-image.png\" style=\"width: 110px; height: 163px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/954446e6-9b84-44cf-b769-6d036e2323d5-image.png\" style=\"width: 140px; height: 163px;\" />&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (04 Sep Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27191,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"The given reactant is p-nitrotoluene.<br><br>Step (i): Reduction with Sn/HCl followed by $OH^-$ converts the $-NO_2$ group to an $-NH_2$ group, yielding p-toluidine.<br><br>Step (ii): Reaction with acetic anhydride, $(CH_3CO)_2O$, protects the amino group by forming N-(4-methylphenyl)acetamide.<br><br>Step (iii): Bromination with $Br_2/AlBr_3$ directs the incoming bromine to the ortho position relative to the strongly activating $-NHCOCH_3$ group (the para position is blocked by the methyl group). This yields 2-bromo-4-methylacetanilide.<br><br>Step (iv): Acid hydrolysis with $H_3O^+$ removes the acetyl group, yielding 2-bromo-4-methylaniline as the major product (P).<br><br>The molecular formula of product P (2-bromo-4-methylaniline) is $C_7H_8NBr$.<br>Molar mass of P = $(7 \\times 12) + (8 \\times 1) + 14 + 80 = 186 \\text{ g mol}^{-1}$.<br><br>In Carius analysis, the bromine in the organic compound is quantitatively converted to silver bromide (AgBr).<br>Molar mass of AgBr = $108 + 80 = 188 \\text{ g mol}^{-1}$.<br><br>Since one molecule of P contains one bromine atom, 1 mole of P produces 1 mole of AgBr.<br>Moles of P in $1.0 \\text{ g} = \\dfrac{1.0}{186} \\text{ mol}$.<br>Moles of AgBr produced = $\\dfrac{1.0}{186} \\text{ mol}$.<br>Mass of AgBr produced = $\\dfrac{1.0}{186} \\times 188 \\text{ g} \\approx 1.01 \\text{ g}$.<br><br>Rounding to the nearest integer, the mass of the AgBr precipitate is 1 g.<br><br>Answer: $1$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (02 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27359,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3e04d31d-0479-4e74-9cc2-ec8dc8be7495-image.png\" style=\"width: 348px; height: 89px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c6a38b50-e618-40d7-b445-eeb7175222ad-image.png\" style=\"width: 321px; height: 89px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/92d223d2-9b49-4b44-b8fe-ef9acced0d1d-image.png\" style=\"width: 336px; height: 89px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/68412030-d1eb-472b-af5d-a00d0fa2140e-image.png\" style=\"width: 340px; height: 82px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/81a03156-6ead-4a91-92e8-a2836b610b0b-image.png\" style=\"width: 670px; height: 244px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27367,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Amines","question":"","options":["(a) and (e)","(b), (c) and (d)","(a) and (d)","(a)"],"answer":1,"solution":"(b), (c) and (d) are the favourable sites for protonation because these are localilsed lone pair electron.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Lwmu50mvZH3wECeU8rTNLyKLaxHV9dS4StktvWf7ItE.original.fullsize.png\">","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (11 Jan Shift 2)","image":null}]